column5: The famous Indian Lake Chain still giving up some good walleye fish in.Slifhtlt slowing down a bit which is normal now.Might have to change my times I fish there.Have had amazing fishing so far this winter.-30 Thursday morning and went at my usuall noon time to fish.-20 on the drive up.To much snow this year but does look beautifull.Drilled one one hole and did catch fish right away and did end up catching 20 or so.Bit slower but expected.Still not bad for 2 hrs.They will get more active again soon.weather change coming soon also.Looks like more snow today and another -30 week.
Ya, gotta be tough life!! Bill

It's been a tough winter both with snow and cold.Few more cold nights and then looks like decent weather coming.We have had 70" of snow so far which is quit a bit.Going to be wet here when we get the thaw but should help with our water levels and fires.Hoping to go out for some trout soon but that mifht be a adventure with the slush on the lakes now to.
